cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic segmentation of trees using a 3D deep learning network. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed network, PointNLM, captures long-range relationships between point clouds and extracts high-level features, which suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of LiDAR point clouds for vegetation segmentation suggests that it may also fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The deep learning approach used for semantic segmentation suggests that it may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the focus on vegetation segmentation suggests that it may also fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
